# set-space-llm.word — a being sets the llm configuration on a space (llm-assigner/ops.js
# set-space-llm DO op). MULTI-MOMENT composite (the writeLlmFields fan-out, now words): the 7-step
# chain fields (slot list, force flags, preferOwn) each land as their OWN do:set-space fact on the
# space reel — one moment per field, exactly as the old handler's per-field doVerb loop.
#
# WORD-SOLE (handler-less, Tabor's no-mirror law): this `.word` is the ONLY path (do.js
# runOpWordToStore runs it via runWordToStore; runAsStore). The host see resolve-llm-config (mode
# "space") is the floor — it reads Space.exists on params.spaceId (SPACE_NOT_FOUND on absence),
# legacy-normalizes, runs the force-flag mutex, validates the slot, and BUILDS the { field, value }
# write list. It lays NO fact; the deeds lay the facts.
#
# The bridge binds `target`, `params` (spaceId + the chain fields), `caller`, `branch`.

When a being sets the llm configuration on a space:
  If no caller, refuse with "set-space-llm requires an authenticated being." as unauthorized.
  see resolve-llm-config(params, caller) as cfg.
  For each w in cfg's writes:
    do set-space on the space $cfg.targetId with { field: $w.field, value: $w.value, merge: false } as wrote.
  Return spaceId: $cfg.targetId.
